@NODE 1 "Reservoir Dogz - Help."
                      @{FG HIGHLIGHT}1. INTRODUCTION TO 'RESERVOIR DOGZ'@{FG TEXT}

  Hi. My name is Gareth Griffiths, and I have a really annoying habit of
  referring to myself in the third-person, so don't be alarmed when I keep
  calling myself Gareth (?!)
  
  Anyway, thanks for purchasing/downloading/finding 'Reservoir Dogz'. It
  really makes the work that Gareth put in worthwhile. But why did Gareth
  make it? Well, after watching the film 'Reservoir Dogs' by Quentin
  Tarantino, Gareth decided to make a game about it. Unfortunately, because
  of copyright laws in Britain and the USA, he could not call the game
  'Reservoir Dogs' without paying a license fee. So he compromised and 
  replaced the second S with a Z. Problem Solved!
  
  He had been dabbling around in AMOS Pro for a while, and had made games
  like Alien Pong Trilogy 2 (reviewed in AF102), and Shoot Out 1 and 2
  (reviewed in AF103 and AF107 respectively). He had already attempted to
  make an Operation Wolf type game, which went under the title Shoot-Out
  (not to be confused with the others described above.) Unfortunately, 
  Gareth did not have enough experience with AMOS to make one back then,
  so he persevered with Shoot Out 1 and 2 (confused yet?) and APT2. 
    Then, while he was lying in bed watching 'Reservoir Dogs' he hit upon
  the idea on how to get it to work. He started coding the very next day,
  and three months later, this is the result!
  
