@NODE 3 "Reservoir Dogz - Help."  
                             @{FG HIGHLIGHT}3. SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS@{FG TEXT}
                             
  The minimum system configuration to run 'Reservoir Dogz' is:
  
       An Amiga
       Workbench/Kickstart 1.3.2 or above
       A mouse (2-buttoned)
       1.3 Megabytes of Chip RAM
       Fast RAM is not required or utilised.
       A MMU or FPU are neither required or utilised.
       
       A hard drive is not required but is recommended.
      
  To install 'Reservoir Dogz' to a @{FG HIGHLIGHT}hard drive@{FG TEXT} then you simply execute the
  hard drive install script in the root directory of the disk. The script
  is called 'HD-Install' and requires the 'Installer' program to be in your
  path. Note that you must have booted from your hard drive for the script
  to work.

  The file 'R_Dogz.scores' contains high score data. If this file is not
  present, then the game will generate one on the fly.
  
  'Reservoir Dogz' has been tested on:
  
  A1200 / 68020 / 10mb / HD / CD / DD / Wb3.0
  A1200 / 68020 / 2mb  / HD /    / DD / Wb3.0
  A1200 / 68030 / 18mb / HD / CD / DD / Wb3.1
  A500+ / 68000 / 2mb  /    /    / DD / Wb2.04
  A500  / 68000 / 2mb  /    /    / DD / Wb1.3.2
  
  It has not been tested on chipsets above 68030, the PPC boards or a
  68010. If 'Reservoir Dogz' fails to work on your setup, and you suspect
  that it is conflicting with your hardware, send system details to us and
  we will attempt to rectify the problem.

